01:48:29,368 --> 01:48:33,029
To the punished animal
this switching was new!

2205
01:48:33,029 --> 01:48:39,070
and at its third repetition he turned his
head in surprise, but was no more heeded

2206
01:48:39,070 --> 01:48:44,039
than were the bluffs and flowers where
he was taking his own

2207
01:48:44,039 --> 01:48:46,678
undirected choice of way.

2208
01:48:46,678 --> 01:48:50,447
He carried her over ground she knew by
heart⁠—Corncliff Mesa,

2209
01:48:50,447 --> 01:48:56,994
Crowheart Butte, Westfall’s Crossing,
Upper Canyon; open land and woodland,

2210
01:48:56,994 --> 01:49:00,394
pines and sagebrush,
all silent and grave and

2211
01:49:00,394 --> 01:49:02,107
lustrous in the sunshine.

2212
01:49:02,107 --> 01:49:06,425
Once and again a ranchman greeted her,
and wondered if she had forgotten who he

2213
01:49:06,425 --> 01:49:12,249
was; once she passed some cowpunchers
with a small herd of steers,

2214
01:49:12,249 --> 01:49:13,932
and they stared after her too.

2215
01:49:13,932 --> 01:49:19,439
Bear Creek narrowed, its mountainsides
drew near, its little falls began to

2216
01:49:19,439 --> 01:49:24,713
rush white in midday shadow,
and the horse suddenly pricked his ears.

2217
01:49:24,713 --> 01:49:28,647
Unguided, he was taking this
advantage to go home.

2218
01:49:28,647 --> 01:49:33,326
Though he had made but little way⁠—a mere
beginning yet⁠—on this trail over to

2219
01:49:33,326 --> 01:49:39,013
Sunk Creek, here was already a Sunk
