2223
01:49:51,082 --> 01:49:55,298
trail as the rider had
dropped them to dismount.

2224
01:49:55,298 --> 01:50:01,248
A cold spring bubbled out beyond the next
rock, and she knew her lover’s horse was

2225
01:50:01,248 --> 01:50:03,372
waiting for him while he drank.

2226
01:50:03,372 --> 01:50:07,111
She pulled at the reins,
but loosed them, for to turn and escape

2227
01:50:07,111 --> 01:50:12,243
now was ridiculous; and riding boldly
round the rock, she came upon

2228
01:50:12,243 --> 01:50:13,444
him by the spring.

2229
01:50:13,444 --> 01:50:17,363
One of his arms hung up to its elbow in
the pool, the other was crooked beside

2230
01:50:17,363 --> 01:50:21,100
his head, but the face was sunk downward
against the shelving rock,

2231
01:50:21,100 --> 01:50:23,815
so that she saw only
his black, tangled hair.

2232
01:50:23,815 --> 01:50:29,109
As her horse snorted and tossed his head
she looked swiftly at Monte,

2233
01:50:29,109 --> 01:50:30,329
as if to question him.

2234
01:50:30,329 --> 01:50:34,597
Seeing now the sweat matted on his coat,
and noting the white rim of his eye,

2235
01:50:34,597 --> 01:50:37,678
she sprang and ran to
the motionless figure.

2236
01:50:37,678 --> 01:50:41,618
