3682
03:11:24,228 --> 03:11:24,348
A

3683
03:11:24,348 --> 03:11:25,971
Stable on the Flat

3684
03:11:25,971 --> 03:11:28,851
When the first landmark,
the lone clump of cottonwoods,

3685
03:11:28,851 --> 03:11:32,051
came at length in sight,
dark and blurred in the gentle rain,

3686
03:11:32,051 --> 03:11:35,854
standing out perhaps a mile beyond the
distant buildings, my whole weary body

3687
03:11:35,854 --> 03:11:37,414
hailed the approach of repose.

3688
03:11:37,414 --> 03:11:40,294
Saving the noon hour,
I had been in the saddle since six,

3689
03:11:40,294 --> 03:11:42,374
and now six was come round again.

3690
03:11:42,374 --> 03:11:45,734
The ranch, my resting-place for this
night, was a ruin⁠—cabin,

3691
03:11:45,734 --> 03:11:46,934
stable, and corral.

3692
03:11:46,934 --> 03:11:50,098
Yet after the twelve hours of pushing on
and on through silence,

3693
03:11:50,098 --> 03:11:52,378
still to have silence,
still to eat and go to sleep in it,

3694
03:11:52,378 --> 03:11:56,218
perfectly fitted the mood of both
my flesh and spirit.

3695
03:11:56,218 --> 03:11:59,209
At noon, when for a while I had thrown
off my long oilskin coat,

3696
03:11:59,209 --> 03:12:01,879
merely the sight of the newspaper half
crowded into my pocket had been a

3697
03:12:01,879 --> 03:12:05,800
displeasing reminder of the railway,
and cities, and affairs.

3698
03:12:05,800 --> 03:12:09,679
But for its possible help to build fires,
it would have come no farther with me.

3699
03:12:09,679 --> 03:12:13,185
The great levels around me lay cooled and
freed of dust by the wet weather,

3700
03:12:13,185 --> 03:12:14,744
and full of sweet airs.

3701
03:12:14,744 --> 03:12:18,981
Far in front the foothills rose through
the rain, indefinite and mystic.

3702
03:12:18,981 --> 03:12:21,441
I wanted no speech with anyone,
nor to be near human beings at all.

3703
03:12:21,441 --> 03:12:24,661
I was steeped in a revery as of the
primal earth; even thoughts themselves

3704
03:12:24,661 --> 03:12:26,865
had almost ceased motion.

3705
03:12:26,865 --> 03:12:31,549
To lie down with wild animals,
with elk and deer, would have made my

3706
03:12:31,549 --> 03:12:33,939
waking dream complete;
and since such dream could not be,

3707
03:12:33,939 --> 03:12:37,139
the cattle around the deserted
buildings, mere dots as yet across

3708
03:12:37,139 --> 03:12:40,670
separating space, were my proper
companions for this evening.

3709
03:12:40,670 --> 03:12:42,979
Tomorrow night I should probably be
camping with the Virginian

3710
03:12:42,979 --> 03:12:43,939
in the foothills.

3711
03:12:43,939 --> 03:12:46,699
At his letter’s bidding I had come
eastward across Idaho,

3712
03:12:46,699 --> 03:12:49,059
abandoning my hunting in the Saw Tooth
Range to make this journey with him

3713
03:12:49,059 --> 03:12:50,379
back through the Tetons.

3714
03:12:50,379 --> 03:12:52,899
It was a trail known to him,
and not to many other honest men.

3715
03:12:52,899 --> 03:12:54,820
Horse Thief Pass was the name
his letter gave it.

3716
03:12:54,820 --> 03:12:57,530
Business (he was always brief) would call
him over there at this time.

3717
03:12:57,530 --> 03:13:00,650
Returning, he must attend to certain
matters in the Wind River country.

3718
03:13:00,650 --> 03:13:03,556
There I could leave by stage for the
railroad, or go on with him the whole

3719
03:13:03,556 --> 03:13:05,021
way back to Sunk Creek.

3720
03:13:05,021 --> 03:13:07,342
He designated for our meeting the forks
of a certain little stream in the

3721
03:13:07,342 --> 03:13:09,533
foothills which today’s ride
had brought in sight.

3722
03:13:09,533 --> 03:13:12,293
There would be no chance for him to
receive an answer from me

3723
03:13:12,293 --> 03:13:13,493
in the intervening time.

3724
03:13:13,493 --> 03:13:17,053
If by a certain day⁠—which was four days
off still⁠—I had not reached the forks,

3725
03:13:17,053 --> 03:13:18,808
he would understand I had other plans.

3726
03:13:18,808 --> 03:13:22,646
To me it was like living back in ages
gone, this way of meeting my friend,

3727
03:13:22,646 --> 03:13:25,846
this choice of a stream so far and
lonely that its very course upon the

3728
03:13:25,846 --> 03:13:27,286
maps was wrongly traced.

3729
03:13:27,286 --> 03:13:30,646
And to leave behind all noise and
mechanisms, and set out at ease,

3730
03:13:30,646 --> 03:13:33,086
slowly, with one packhorse,
into the wilderness,

3731
03:13:33,086 --> 03:13:36,207
made me feel that the ancient earth was
indeed my mother and that I had found

3732
03:13:36,207 --> 03:13:40,128
her again after being lost among
houses, customs, and restraints.

3733
03:13:40,128 --> 03:13:44,702
I should arrive three days early at the
forks⁠—three days of margin seeming to

3734
03:13:44,702 --> 03:13:46,989
me a wise precaution
against delays unforeseen.

3735
03:13:46,989 --> 03:13:50,484
If the Virginian were not there,
good; I could fish and be happy.

3736
03:13:50,484 --> 03:13:54,199
If he were there but not ready to start,
good; I could still fish and be happy.

3737
03:13:54,199 --> 03:13:58,543
And remembering my Eastern helplessness
in the year when we had met first,

3738
03:13:58,543 --> 03:14:01,384
I enjoyed thinking how I had
come to be trusted.

3739
03:14:01,384 --> 03:14:04,304
In those days I had not been allowed to
go from the ranch for so much as an

3740
03:14:04,304 --> 03:14:08,184
afternoon’s ride unless tied to him by a
string, so to speak;

3741
03:14:08,184 --> 03:14:11,027
now I was crossing unmapped
spaces with no guidance.

3742
03:14:11,027 --> 03:14:13,627
The man who could do this was scarce
any longer a “tenderfoot.”

3743
03:14:13,627 --> 03:14:15,070
My vision, as I rode,
took in serenely the dim foothills⁠—

3744
03:14:15,070 --> 03:14:19,390
tomorrow’s goal⁠—and nearer in the vast
wet plain the clump of cottonwoods,

3745
03:14:19,390 --> 03:14:23,430
and still nearer my lodging for tonight
with the dotted cattle round it.

3746
03:14:23,430 --> 03:14:24,990
And now my horse neighed.

3747
03:14:24,990 --> 03:14:28,906
I felt his gait freshen for the journey’s
end, and leaning to pat his neck I

3748
03:14:28,906 --> 03:14:32,660
noticed his ears no longer slack and
inattentive, but pointing forward to

3749
03:14:32,660 --> 03:14:35,180
where food and rest awaited both of us.

3750
03:14:35,180 --> 03:14:40,410
Twice he neighed, impatiently and long;
and as he quickened his gait still more,

3751
03:14:40,410 --> 03:14:43,931
the packhorse did the same,
and I realized that there was about me

3752
03:14:43,931 --> 03:14:46,440
still a spice of the tenderfoot:
those dots were not cattle;

3753
03:14:46,440 --> 03:14:47,782
they were horses.

3754
03:14:47,782 --> 03:14:49,622
My horse had put me in the wrong.

3755
03:14:49,622 --> 03:14:53,847
He had known his kind from afar,
and was hastening to them.

3756
03:14:53,847 --> 03:14:58,021
The plainsman’s eye was not yet mine;
and I smiled a little as I rode.

3757
03:14:58,021 --> 03:15:01,942
When was I going to know,
as by instinct, the different look of

3758
03:15:01,942 --> 03:15:05,099
horses and cattle across some two or
three miles of plain?

3759
03:15:05,099 --> 03:15:05,939
These miles we finished soon.

3760
03:15:05,939 --> 03:15:08,540
The buildings changed in their aspect as
they grew to my approach,

3761
03:15:08,540 --> 03:15:11,739
showing their desolation more clearly,
and in some way bringing

3762
03:15:11,739 --> 03:15:13,339
apprehension into my mood.

3763
03:15:13,339 --> 03:15:16,571
And around them the horses,
too, all standing with ears erect,

3764
03:15:16,571 --> 03:15:20,403
watching me as I came⁠—there was
something about them;

3765
03:15:20,403 --> 03:15:21,915
or was it the silence?

3766
03:15:21,915 --> 03:15:26,334
For the silence which I had liked until
now seemed suddenly to be made too great

3767
03:15:26,334 --> 03:15:29,055
by the presence of the
deserted buildings.

3768
03:15:29,055 --> 03:15:32,680
And then the door of the stable opened,
and men came out and stood,

3769
03:15:32,680 --> 03:15:34,395
also watching me arrive.

3770
03:15:34,395 --> 03:15:38,098
By the time I was dismounting
more were there.

3771
03:15:38,098 --> 03:15:42,578
It was senseless to feel as unpleasant as
I did, and I strove to give to them a

3772
03:15:42,578 --> 03:15:45,342
greeting that should sound easy.

3773
03:15:45,342 --> 03:15:50,318
I told them that I hoped there was room
for one more here tonight.

3774
03:15:50,318 --> 03:15:53,483
Some of them had answered my greeting,
but none of them answered this;

3775
03:15:53,483 --> 03:15:56,934
and as I began to be sure that I
recognized several of their strangely

3776
03:15:56,934 --> 03:16:00,894
imperturbable faces,
the Virginian came from the stable;

3777
03:16:00,894 --> 03:16:06,922
and at that welcome sight my
relief spoke out instantly.

3778
03:16:06,922 --> 03:16:09,032
“I am here, you see!”

3779
03:16:09,032 --> 03:16:10,616
“Yes, I do see.”

3780
03:16:10,616 --> 03:16:14,918
I looked hard at him,
for in his voice was the same

3781
03:16:14,918 --> 03:16:18,312
strangeness that I felt
in everything around me.

3782
03:16:18,312 --> 03:16:21,351
But he was looking at his companions.

3783
03:16:21,351 --> 03:16:24,897
“This gentleman is all
right,” he told them.

3784
03:16:24,897 --> 03:16:29,739
“That may be,” said one whom I now knew
that I had seen before at Sunk Creek;

3785
03:16:29,739 --> 03:16:31,387
“but he was not due tonight.”

3786
03:16:31,387 --> 03:16:33,114
“Nor tomorrow,” said another.

3787
03:16:33,114 --> 03:16:36,086
“Nor yet the day after,” a third added.

3788
03:16:36,086 --> 03:16:38,123
The Virginian fell into his drawl.

3789
03:16:38,123 --> 03:16:41,582
“None of you was ever early
for anything, I presume.”

3790
03:16:41,582 --> 03:16:43,753
One retorted, laughing,
“Oh, we’re not suspicioning

3791
03:16:43,753 --> 03:16:45,417
you of complicity.”

3792
03:16:45,417 --> 03:16:51,289
And another, “Not even when we remember
how thick you and Steve used to be.”

3793
03:16:51,289 --> 03:16:54,489
Whatever jokes they meant by this he did
not receive as jokes.

3794
03:16:54,489 --> 03:16:59,831
I saw something like a wince pass over
his face, and a flush follow it.

3795
03:16:59,831 --> 03:17:01,372
But he now spoke to me.

3796
03:17:01,372 --> 03:17:06,932
“We expected to be through
before this,” he began.

3797
03:17:06,932 --> 03:17:09,323
“I’m right sorry you have come tonight.

3798
03:17:09,323 --> 03:17:12,083
I know you’d have preferred to keep away.”

3799
03:17:12,083 --> 03:17:17,917
“We want him to explain himself,”
put in one of the others.

3800
03:17:17,917 --> 03:17:22,070
“If he satisfies us, he’s
free to go away.”

3801
03:17:22,070 --> 03:17:23,670
“Free to go away!”

3802
03:17:23,670 --> 03:17:25,470
I now exclaimed.

3803
03:17:25,470 --> 03:17:30,337
But at the indulgence in their frontier
smile I cooled down.

3804
03:17:30,337 --> 03:17:36,735
“Gentlemen,” I said, “I don’t know why my
movements interest you so much.

3805
03:17:36,735 --> 03:17:39,771
It’s quite a compliment!

3806
03:17:39,771 --> 03:17:43,805
May I get under shelter while I explain?”

3807
03:17:43,805 --> 03:17:48,529
No request could have been more natural,
for the rain had now begun to

3808
03:17:48,529 --> 03:17:50,853
fall in straight floods.

3809
03:17:50,853 --> 03:17:54,655
Yet there was a pause before one of them
said, “He might as well.”

3810
03:17:54,655 --> 03:17:59,849
The Virginian chose to say nothing more;
but he walked beside me into the stable.

3811
03:17:59,849 --> 03:18:03,590
Two men sat there together,
and a third guarded them.

3812
03:18:03,590 --> 03:18:07,440
At that sight I knew suddenly what I had
stumbled upon; and on the impulse I

3813
03:18:07,440 --> 03:18:10,151
murmured to the Virginian,
“You’re hanging them tomorrow.”

3814
03:18:10,151 --> 03:18:11,351
He kept his silence.

3815
03:18:11,351 --> 03:18:13,889
“You may have three guesses,”
said a man behind me.

3816
03:18:13,889 --> 03:18:16,243
But I did not need them.

3817
03:18:16,243 --> 03:18:20,478
And in the recoil of my insight the clump
of cottonwoods came into my

3818
03:18:20,478 --> 03:18:22,078
mind, black and grim.

3819
03:18:22,078 --> 03:18:24,201
No other trees high enough
grew within ten miles.

3820
03:18:24,201 --> 03:18:27,398
This, then, was the business that the
Virginian’s letter had

3821
03:18:27,398 --> 03:18:29,548
so curtly mentioned.

3822
03:18:29,548 --> 03:18:35,213
My eyes went into all corners of the
stable, but no other prisoners were

3823
03:18:35,213 --> 03:18:36,484
here.

3824
03:18:36,484 --> 03:18:40,804
I half expected to see Trampas,
and I half feared to see Shorty

3825
03:18:40,804 --> 03:18:46,565
; for poor stupid Shorty’s honesty had
not been proof against frontier

3826
03:18:46,565 --> 03:18:51,366
temptations, and he had fallen away from
the company of his old friends.

3827
03:18:51,366 --> 03:18:55,046
Often of late I had heard talk at Sunk
Creek of breaking up a certain gang of

3828
03:18:55,046 --> 03:18:59,167
horse and cattle thieves that stole in
one Territory and sold in the next,

3829
03:18:59,167 --> 03:19:02,060
and knew where to hide
in the mountains between.

3830
03:19:02,060 --> 03:19:06,474
And now it had come to the point;
forces had been gathered,

3831
03:19:06,474 --> 03:19:10,341
a long expedition made,
and here they were, successful under the

3832
03:19:10,341 --> 03:19:14,469
Virginian’s lead, but a little
later than their calculations.

3833
03:19:14,469 --> 03:19:19,506
And here was I, a little too early,
and a witness in consequence.

3834
03:19:19,506 --> 03:19:23,069
My presence seemed a simple thing to
account for; but when I had thus

3835
03:19:23,069 --> 03:19:26,869
accounted for it, one of them
said with good nature:⁠—

3836
03:19:26,869 --> 03:19:29,789
“So you find us here,
and we find you here.

3837
03:19:29,789 --> 03:19:31,549
Which is the most surprised, I wonder?”

3838
03:19:31,549 --> 03:19:34,131
“There’s no telling,”
said I, keeping as amiable as I could;

3839
03:19:34,131 --> 03:19:36,451
“nor any telling which objects the
most.”

3840
03:19:36,451 --> 03:19:38,851
“Oh, there’s no objection here.

3841
03:19:38,851 --> 03:19:40,356
You’re welcome to stay.

3842
03:19:40,356 --> 03:19:42,571
But not welcome to go, I expect.

3843
03:19:42,571 --> 03:19:44,519
He ain’t welcome to go, is he?”

3844
03:19:44,519 --> 03:19:48,107
By the answers that their faces gave him
it was plain that I was not.

3845
03:19:48,107 --> 03:19:51,088
“Not till we are through,” said one.

3846
03:19:51,088 --> 03:19:53,778
“He needn’t to see anything,”
’ another added.

3847
03:19:53,778 --> 03:19:57,891
“Better sleep late tomorrow morning,”
a third suggested to me.

3848
03:19:57,891 --> 03:20:00,642
I did not wish to stay here.

3849
03:20:00,642 --> 03:20:05,543
I could have made some sort of camp apart
from them before dark;

3850
03:20:05,543 --> 03:20:08,946
but in the face of their needless
caution I was helpless.

3851
03:20:08,946 --> 03:20:13,582
I made no attempt to inquire what kind of
spy they imagined I could be,

3852
03:20:13,582 --> 03:20:17,263
what sort of rescue I could bring in
this lonely country;

3853
03:20:17,263 --> 03:20:21,107
my too early appearance seemed to be all
that they looked at.

3854
03:20:21,107 --> 03:20:22,980
And again my eyes sought the prisoners.

3855
03:20:22,980 --> 03:20:24,907
Certainly there were only two.

3856
03:20:24,907 --> 03:20:29,629
One was chewing tobacco,
and talking now and then to his guard as

3857
03:20:29,629 --> 03:20:31,459
if nothing were the matter.

3858
03:20:31,459 --> 03:20:34,982
The other sat dull in silence,
not moving his eyes;

3859
03:20:34,982 --> 03:20:38,002
but his face worked,
and I noticed how he continually

3860
03:20:38,002 --> 03:20:41,095
moistened his dry lips.

3861
03:20:41,095 --> 03:20:44,895
As I looked at these doomed prisoners,
whose fate I was invited to sleep

3862
03:20:44,895 --> 03:20:47,615
through tomorrow morning,
the one who was chewing

3863
03:20:47,615 --> 03:20:49,295
quietly nodded to me.

3864
03:20:49,295 --> 03:20:51,615
“You don’t remember me?”

3865
03:20:51,615 --> 03:20:52,368
he said.

3866
03:20:52,368 --> 03:20:53,686
It was Steve!

3867
03:20:53,686 --> 03:20:54,846
Steve of Medicine Bow!

3868
03:20:54,846 --> 03:20:57,046
The pleasant Steve of my first
evening in the West.

3869
03:20:57,046 --> 03:21:01,980
Some change of beard had delayed my
instant recognition of his face.

3870
03:21:01,980 --> 03:21:03,600
Here he sat sentenced to die.

3871
03:21:03,600 --> 03:21:06,080
A shock, chill and painful,
deprived me of speech.

3872
03:21:06,080 --> 03:21:07,391
He had no such weak feelings.

3873
03:21:07,391 --> 03:21:10,158
“Have yu’ been to Medicine Bow lately?”

3874
03:21:10,158 --> 03:21:11,634
he inquired.

3875
03:21:11,634 --> 03:21:13,637
“That’s getting to be quite a while ago.”

3876
03:21:13,637 --> 03:21:15,117
I assented.

3877
03:21:15,117 --> 03:21:19,121
I should have liked to say something
natural and kind, but words stuck

3878
03:21:19,121 --> 03:21:23,797
against my will, and I stood awkward and
ill at ease, noticing idly that the

3879
03:21:23,797 --> 03:21:27,277
silent one wore a gray
flannel shirt like mine.

3880
03:21:27,277 --> 03:21:30,687
Steve looked me over,
and saw in my pocket the newspaper which

3881
03:21:30,687 --> 03:21:34,517
I had brought from the railroad and on
which I had pencilled a few expenses.

3882
03:21:34,517 --> 03:21:37,757
He asked me, Would I mind letting him
have it for a while?

3883
03:21:37,757 --> 03:21:40,077
And I gave it to him eagerly,
begging him to keep it as

3884
03:21:40,077 --> 03:21:41,686
long as he wanted.

3885
03:21:41,686 --> 03:21:43,330
I was overeager in my embarrassment.

3886
03:21:43,330 --> 03:21:47,481
“You need not return it at all,”
I said; “those notes are nothing.

3887
03:21:47,481 --> 03:21:47,521
Do keep it.”

3888
03:21:47,521 --> 03:21:49,481
He gave me a short glance and a smile.

3889
03:21:49,481 --> 03:21:52,344
“Thank you,” he said;
“I’ll not need it beyond

3890
03:21:52,344 --> 03:21:52,794
tomorrow morning.”

3891
03:21:52,794 --> 03:21:53,726
And he began to search through it.

3892
03:21:53,726 --> 03:21:58,264
“Jake’s election is considered sure,”
he said to his companion,

3893
03:21:58,264 --> 03:21:59,864
who made no response.

3894
03:21:59,864 --> 03:22:02,804
“Well, Fremont County owes it to Jake.”

3895
03:22:02,804 --> 03:22:05,400
And I left him interested
in the local news.

3896
03:22:05,400 --> 03:22:08,564
Dead men I have seen not a few times,
even some lying pale and terrible after

3897
03:22:08,564 --> 03:22:13,385
violent ends, and the edge of this wears
off; but I hope I shall never again have

3898
03:22:13,385 --> 03:22:15,585
to be in the company with men
waiting to be killed.

3899
03:22:15,585 --> 03:22:18,985
By this time tomorrow the gray flannel
shirt would be buttoned round a corpse.

3900
03:22:18,985 --> 03:22:21,316
Until what moment would Steve chew?

3901
03:22:21,316 --> 03:22:25,276
Against such fancies as these I managed
presently to barricade my mind,

3902
03:22:25,276 --> 03:22:30,029
but I made a plea to be allowed to pass
the night elsewhere,

3903
03:22:30,029 --> 03:22:33,322
and I suggested the adjacent cabin.

3904
03:22:33,322 --> 03:22:36,562
By their faces I saw that my words merely
helped their distrust of me.

3905
03:22:36,562 --> 03:22:40,655
The cabin leaked too much,
they said; I would sleep drier here.

3906
03:22:40,655 --> 03:22:44,102
One man gave it to me more directly:
“If you figured on camping in this

3907
03:22:44,102 --> 03:22:45,865
stable, what has changed your mind?”

3908
03:22:45,865 --> 03:22:49,629
How could I tell them that I shrunk from
any contact with what they were doing,

3909
03:22:49,629 --> 03:22:53,002
although I knew that only so could
justice be dealt in this country?

3910
03:22:53,002 --> 03:22:57,448
Their wholesome frontier nerves knew
nothing of such refinements.

3911
03:22:57,448 --> 03:23:00,171
But the Virginian understood part of it.

3912
03:23:00,171 --> 03:23:02,528
“I am right sorry for
your annoyance,” he said.

3913
03:23:02,528 --> 03:23:06,419
And now I noticed he was under a
constraint very different from the

3914
03:23:06,419 --> 03:23:08,110
ease of the others.

3915
03:23:08,110 --> 03:23:11,550
After the twelve hours’ ride my bones
were hungry for rest.

3916
03:23:11,550 --> 03:23:17,461
I spread my blankets on some straw in a
stall by myself and rolled up in them;

3917
03:23:17,461 --> 03:23:21,956
yet I lay growing broader awake,
every inch of weariness stricken

3918
03:23:21,956 --> 03:23:24,144
from my excited senses.

3919
03:23:24,144 --> 03:23:27,016
For a while they sat over their councils,
whispering cautiously,

3920
03:23:27,016 --> 03:23:31,016
so that I was made curious to hear them
by not being able; was it the names of

3921
03:23:31,016 --> 03:23:36,969
Trampas and Shorty that were once or
twice spoken⁠—I could not be sure.

3922
03:23:36,969 --> 03:23:39,972
I heard the whisperers cease and separate.

3923
03:23:39,972 --> 03:23:43,800
I heard their boots as they cast them
off upon the ground.

3924
03:23:43,800 --> 03:23:48,865
And I heard the breathing of slumber
begin and grow in the interior silence.

3925
03:23:48,865 --> 03:23:52,465
To one after one sleep came,
but not to me.

3926
03:23:52,465 --> 03:23:56,064
Outside, the dull fall of the rain beat
evenly, and in some angle dripped the

3927
03:23:56,064 --> 03:23:58,785
spouting pulses of a leak.

3928
03:23:58,785 --> 03:24:03,119
Sometimes a cold air blew in,
bearing with it the keen wet

3929
03:24:03,119 --> 03:24:05,650
odor of the sagebrush.

3930
03:24:05,650 --> 03:24:09,893
On hundreds of other nights this perfume
had been my last waking remembrance;

3931
03:24:09,893 --> 03:24:15,924
it had seemed to help drowsiness;
and now I lay staring, thinking of this.

3932
03:24:15,924 --> 03:24:19,339
Twice through the hours the thieves
shifted their positions with clumsy

3933
03:24:19,339 --> 03:24:22,278
sounds, exchanging muted
words with their guard.

3934
03:24:22,278 --> 03:24:26,020
So, often, had I heard other companions
move and mutter in the darkness

3935
03:24:26,020 --> 03:24:28,476
and lie down again.

3936
03:24:28,476 --> 03:24:32,680
It was the very naturalness and usualness
of every fact of the night⁠—the stable

3937
03:24:32,680 --> 03:24:35,120
straw, the rain outside,
my familiar blankets,

3938
03:24:35,120 --> 03:24:40,178
the cool visits of the wind⁠—and with
all this the thought of Steve chewing

3939
03:24:40,178 --> 03:24:43,980
and the man in the gray flannel shirt,
that made the hours unearthly and strung

3940
03:24:43,980 --> 03:24:45,218
me tight with suspense.

3941
03:24:45,218 --> 03:24:49,258
And at last I heard someone get up
and begin to dress.

3942
03:24:49,258 --> 03:24:53,181
In a little while I saw light suddenly
through my closed eyelids,

3943
03:24:53,181 --> 03:24:54,563
and then darkness shut
again abruptly upon them.

3944
03:24:54,563 --> 03:24:57,041
They had swung in a lantern and
found me by mistake.

3945
03:24:57,041 --> 03:24:59,121
I was the only one they did
not wish to rouse.

3946
03:24:59,121 --> 03:25:01,441
Moving and quiet talking set up around
me, and they began to go

3947
03:25:01,441 --> 03:25:02,079
out of the stable.

